Electrical Equipment

Company Overview of Professional Power Products, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Professional Power Products, Inc. designs, manufactures, and sells custom engineered integrated electrical power generation systems. It offers enclosure products, including drop over style, weatherproof, and sound attenuated enclosures, as well as field erection kits for use in reciprocating and gas turbine generator set markets; power modules; single, double, and triple axel tow behind trailers with optional integral double wall fuel tanks; and fuel tanks with various capacities. The company also provides load banks that are used in testing electrical power sources; electrical control panels and equipment; circuit breakers, which are used for engines, generators, pumps, and fuel level contr...
Professional Power Products, Inc. designs, manufactures, and sells custom engineered integrated electrical power generation systems. It offers enclosure products, including drop over style, weatherproof, and sound attenuated enclosures, as well as field erection kits for use in reciprocating and gas turbine generator set markets; power modules; single, double, and triple axel tow behind trailers with optional integral double wall fuel tanks; and fuel tanks with various capacities. The company also provides load banks that are used in testing electrical power sources; electrical control panels and equipment; circuit breakers, which are used for engines, generators, pumps, and fuel level control; and switchgears that are used for distribution, paralleling, and motor control applications in utility, industrial, and critical power industries. In addition, it offers a range of engineering design and consulting support, technical support, and installation services. The company’s products have applications in utility, offshore oil and gas platforms, hospitals, and electrical products and systems, as well as in diesel and natural gas power generation markets. Professional Power Products, Inc. was founded in 1992 and is headquartered in Darien, Wisconsin. As of April 1, 2014, Professional Power Products, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Power Solutions International, Inc.
Detailed Description


